<eesti>&Otilde;hus&otilde;iduki sundmaandamise kord </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for Forced Landing of Aircraft </inglise>
<eesti>Vabariigi Valitsuse 25. veebruari 2000. a m&auml;&auml;rus nr 71 </eesti>
<inglise>Government of the Republic Regulation No. 71 of 25 February 2000 </inglise>
<eesti>(RT I 2000, 15, 108), </eesti>
<inglise>(RT (1) I 2000, 15, 108), </inglise>
<eesti>j&otilde;ustunud 4. m&auml;rtsil 2000. a. </eesti>
<inglise>entered into force 4 March 2000. </inglise>
<eesti>M&auml;&auml;rus kehtestatakse "Lennundusseaduse" (RT I 1999, 26, 376) &sect; 52 l&otilde;ike 2 alusel &otilde;hus&otilde;iduki sundmaandamise korra rakendamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>This Regulation is established on the basis of subsection 52 (2) of the Aviation Act (RT (2) I 1999, 26, 376) to implement the procedure for forced landing of aircraft. </inglise>
<eesti>1. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 1 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esolev kord s&auml;testab tsiviil&otilde;hus&otilde;iduki (edaspidi &otilde;hus&otilde;iduk) sundmaandamise korra koosk&otilde;las Rahvusvahelise Tsiviillennunduse Organisatsiooni (RTO) 1944. a Chicago rahvusvahelise tsiviillennunduse konventsiooni artikliga 5 ja lisaga (Annex) 2 ning sisaldab RTO dokumendi 9433 p&otilde;him&otilde;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>This Procedure provides for the procedure for the forced landing of civil aircraft (hereinafter aircraft) in accordance with Article 5 and Annex 2 to the 1944 Chicago Convention on International Civil Aviation and contains the principles of the ICAO Doc 9433. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;hus&otilde;iduki sundmaandamist k&auml;sitatakse &otilde;hus&otilde;iduki lendu sekkumisena ning see on &auml;&auml;rmine abin&otilde;u lennuohutuse ning julgeoleku ja avaliku korra tagamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>The forced landing of aircraft is deemed to be intervention in the flight of an aircraft and it is an extreme measure to ensure flight safety and security and public order. </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Sundmaandamise korraldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Organisation of Forced Landing </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Sundmaandamist v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda &otilde;hus&otilde;iduki kaptenilt lennujuht, kes on saanud vastava korralduse lennuliikluse juhtimise teenistuse vanemlennujuhilt ja/v&otilde;i teenistuse &uuml;lemalt, ning kelle vastutusalas &otilde;hus&otilde;iduk asub, kasutades selleks raadiosidet ja vajadusel raadiosagedust 121,5 MHz. </eesti>
<inglise>An air traffic controller has the right to demand the forced landing of an aircraft located in his or her area of responsibility from the pilot-in-command of the aircraft after receiving a corresponding order from the senior air traffic controller and/or the chief of the air traffic control service; the air traffic controller shall communicate with the pilot-in-command of the aircraft by using radiotelephony at the radio frequency of 121,5 MHz, as necessary. </inglise>
<eesti>Ettepaneku &otilde;hus&otilde;iduki sundmaandamiseks v&otilde;ivad lennuliikluse juhtimise teenistusele teha Kaitseministeeriumi ja Siseministeeriumi vastavad ametkonnad. </eesti>
<inglise>Relevant agencies of the Ministry of Defence and the Ministry of Internal Affairs have the right to propose the forced landing of an aircraft to an air traffic control service. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui lennujuht saab korralduse &otilde;hus&otilde;iduki maandamiseks, peab ta kohe v&otilde;tma tarvitusele k&otilde;ik meetmed, et: </eesti>
<inglise>After receiving an order for the forced landing of an aircraft, the air traffic controller shall immediately take all measures to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) informeerida k&otilde;nesoleva &otilde;hus&otilde;iduki kaptenit n&otilde;udest maanduda selleks m&auml;&auml;ratud lennuv&auml;ljal; </eesti>
<inglise>1) inform the pilot-in-command of the aircraft concerned of the demand to land at the designated aerodrome; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tagada sellele &otilde;hus&otilde;idukile kogu informatsioon, mis on n&otilde;utav m&auml;&auml;ratud lennuv&auml;ljale lennuks ja seal maandumiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) ensure that all information required for flying to and landing at the designated aerodrome is forwarded to the aircraft; </inglise>
<eesti>3) edastada &otilde;hus&otilde;iduki kaptenile k&otilde;ik vajalikud korraldused ning navigeerimisjuhendid kuni &otilde;hus&otilde;iduki maandumiseni m&auml;&auml;ratud lennuv&auml;ljal koordineeritult riiklike ametkondade ja asjasse puutuvate lennuliiklusteenistustega, kelle vastutusalaks olevas &otilde;huruumis toimuvat lennutegevust v&otilde;ib nimetatud juhtum m&otilde;jutada. </eesti>
<inglise>3) forward all necessary orders and navigational guidance to the pilot-in-command of the aircraft until the aircraft lands on the designated aerodrome, and co-ordinate such orders and guidance with the state agencies and relevant air traffic services whose area of responsibility includes air space where air traffic operations may be affected by the given incident. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui lennujuhil endal pole v&otilde;imalik edastada &otilde;hus&otilde;iduki kaptenile sundmaandumise korraldust ja sellega kaasnevaid juhiseid, tuleb selleks kasutada teisi lennuliiklusteenistuse &uuml;ksusi ja n&auml;htavaid valgus- v&otilde;i muid signaale. </eesti>
<inglise>If the air traffic controller is unable to personally forward the order for forced landing and related instructions to the pilot-in-command of the aircraft, then other air traffic service units and visible light or other signals shall be used for such purposes. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;hus&otilde;iduki sundmaandamisega seotud teadete edasiandmiseks v&otilde;ib kasutada ka teisi &otilde;hus&otilde;idukeid, kui selgub, et neid teateid ei &otilde;nnestu edastada raadiosidet kasutades. </eesti>
<inglise>Other aircraft may be used to forward information related to the forced landing of an aircraft if it becomes evident that it is impossible to forward such information by radiotelephony. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;hus&otilde;iduki kaptenile antavad korraldused peavad olema &uuml;heselt arusaadavad ja nende j&auml;rgimine peab tagama lennuohutuse s&auml;ilimise igal lennuetapil. </eesti>
<inglise>The orders forwarded to the pilot-in-command of the aircraft shall be unambiguous, and the following such orders shall ensure air safety at every stage of the flight. </inglise>
<eesti>Selleks tuleb arvesse v&otilde;tta, et: </eesti>
<inglise>The following shall be taken into consideration: </inglise>
<eesti>1) maandumiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud lennuv&auml;li oleks sobiv seda t&uuml;&uuml;pi &otilde;hus&otilde;iduki ohutuks maandumiseks, kusjuures tsiviil&otilde;hus&otilde;iduki puhul peab sellise lennuraja pikkus olema v&auml;hemalt 2500 m; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the designated aerodrome shall be suitable for the safe landing of the type of aircraft concerned; if the aircraft is a civil aircraft, the designated aerodrome shall have a runway with a length equivalent to at least 2500 m; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &uuml;mbritsev maastik v&otilde;imaldaks sooritada ringlendu, j&auml;rgida l&auml;henemise ja katkestatud l&auml;henemise protseduure; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the surrounding terrain shall be suitable for circling, approach and missed approach manoeuvres; </inglise>
<eesti>3) maandatav &otilde;hus&otilde;iduk suunataks lennuv&auml;ljale, millele lendamiseks tal on piisav kogus k&uuml;tust; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the aircraft to be landed has sufficient fuel remaining to reach the aerodrome to which it is directed; </inglise>
<eesti>4) v&otilde;imaluse korral m&auml;&auml;rataks sundmaandumiseks lennuv&auml;li, mille andmed sisalduvad Eesti aeronavigatsioonilise teabe kogumikus (AIP); </eesti>
<inglise>4) if possible, the aerodrome designated for the forced landing shall be selected from among the aerodromes regarding which data has been included in the Estonian aeronautical information publication (AIP); </inglise>
<eesti>5) &otilde;hus&otilde;idukit ei juhitaks tingimustesse, kus n&auml;htavus v&auml;heneb allapoole visuaallennuks vajalikku miinimumi, kui on vajalik lennu j&auml;tkamine visuaaltingimustes; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the aircraft is not led into conditions where the visibility may be reduced below the minimum visual flight meteorological conditions, if it is necessary to continue flight in visual meteorological conditions; </inglise>
<eesti>6) &otilde;hus&otilde;iduki maandumiseks vajalikud ja n&otilde;utavad man&ouml;&ouml;vrid ei m&otilde;jutaks lennuohutust juhul, kui v&auml;heneb oluliselt &otilde;hus&otilde;iduki lennuk&otilde;lblikkus. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the manoeuvres necessary and required for the forced landing of the aircraft do not impair flight safety, in case the airworthiness of the aircraft is considerably reduced. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui &otilde;hus&otilde;iduk kavatsetakse sundmaandada &otilde;hus&otilde;iduki kaptenile tundmatul lennuv&auml;ljal, peab talle j&auml;tma piisavalt aega maandumise ettevalmistamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>If the intended landing of the aircraft is to be carried out at an aerodrome unfamiliar to the pilot-in-command of the aircraft, the pilot-in-command shall be left enough time to prepare for the landing. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsuse maandumise ohutuse kohta teeb &otilde;hus&otilde;iduki kapten. </eesti>
<inglise>The pilot-in-command of the aircraft shall decide whether it is safe to land the aircraft. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;hus&otilde;iduki kapten, kes on saanud korralduse maandumiseks, peab: </eesti>
<inglise>The pilot-in-command of the aircraft who has received an order for the landing of the aircraft shall: </inglise>
<eesti>1) maanduma lennujuhi v&otilde;i teiste &otilde;hus&otilde;idukite kaptenite poolt antud juhiste ja lennureeglites s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uete kohaselt; </eesti>
<inglise>1) land the aircraft in adherence with the instructions of the air traffic controller or pilots-in-command of other aircraft and in compliance with the requirements provided for in the rules of the air; </inglise>
<eesti>2) valima sekundaarradari transponderil koodi A 7700, kui lennujuht ei ole andnud teistsugust korraldust. </eesti>
<inglise>2) if equipped with secondary radar transponder, select Mode A, Code 7700, unless otherwise instructed by the air traffic controller. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;hus&otilde;iduki kaptenit ei tohi sundida &otilde;hus&otilde;idukit maandama, kui on kindlalt teada, et see on ohuolukorras v&otilde;i tema tehniline seisund ei v&otilde;imalda &otilde;hus&otilde;iduki kapteni arvates ohutult j&auml;rgida maandumiseks saadud korraldusi. </eesti>
<inglise>The pilot-in-command of the aircraft shall not be compelled to land the aircraft if it is certain that the aircraft is in danger, or, according to the pilot-in-command's opinion, the technical condition of the aircraft does not allow to safely follow the orders given for landing. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;hus&otilde;iduki sundmaandamises osalenud lennuliiklusteenistused esitavad kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul Lennuametile t&auml;ieliku aruande &otilde;hus&otilde;iduki sundmaandamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>The air traffic services involved in the forced landing of an aircraft shall submit a full report on the forced landing to the Civil Aviation Administration within three working days after the forced landing. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;lisriigi &otilde;hus&otilde;iduki sundmaandamisest teatab Lennuamet &otilde;hus&otilde;iduki registreerinud riigi lennundusametkonnale. </eesti>
<inglise>The Civil Aviation Administration shall forward information concerning the forced landing of an aircraft of a foreign state to the appropriate civil aviation agency of the state of registration of the aircraft. (1) RTL = Riigi Teatja Lisa = Appendix to the State Gazette </inglise>

